0by%20their%20father's%20side.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERobert%20F.%20Kennedy%20Jr.%20was%20later%20a%20pallbearer%20at%20his%20father's%20funeral%2C%20joined%20by%20Astronaut%20John%20Glenn%20and%20former%20Defense%20Secretary%20Robert%20McNamara.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Robert%20F.%20Kennedy%20Jr.%20(front%20right)%20helps%20carry%20his%20father's%20casket%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F664c9fdb14fb5b23cc5e9b00%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22686%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERobert%20F.%20Kennedy%20Jr.%20was%20one%20of%20the%20pallbearers%20in%20his%20father's%20funeral.%3Cp%3EMichael%20Ochs%20Archives%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%2014-year-old%20never%20returned%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgeorgetown-prep-school-brett-kavanaugh-neil-gorsuch-2018-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGeorgetown%20Prep%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20now%20counts%20two%20Supreme%20Court%20justices%20and%20multiple%20lawmakers%20among%20its%20influential%20alumni.%20Robert%20F.%20Kennedy%20Jr.%20bounced%20between%20three%20private%20schools%20before%20graduating%20from%20high%20school.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20Millbrook%20School%20in%20New%20York%2C%20he%20briefly%20kept%20a%20lion%20cub%20gifted%20to%20him%20by%20former%20%26quot%3BTonight%20Show%26quot%3B%20host%20Jack%20Paar.%20Kennedy%20was%20forced%20to%20find%20a%20new%20home%20for%20the%20animal%2C%20aptly%20named%20Mtoto%20Mbaya%2C%20%26quot%3BBoy%20Boy%26quot%3B%20in%20Swahili%2C%20after%20a%20string%20of%20incidents%2C%20including%20when%20it%20bit%20the%20backside%20of%20the%20school's%20zoo%20keeper%2C%20according%20to%20%26quot%3BRobert%20F.%20Kennedy%20Jr.%20and%20the%20Dark%20Side%20of%20the%20Dream%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20unauthorized%202015%20biography.%20It%20wasn't%20the%20animal%20that%20got%20him%20kicked%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKennedy%20had%20begun%20to%20use%20drugs%20and%20not%20just%20marijuana%2C%20according%20to%20the%202015%20book.%20Officials%20became%20increasingly%20concerned%20that%20they%20would%20be%20held%20responsible%20if%20another%20Kennedy%20died%20on%20their%20watch.%20Years%20later%2C%20Kennedy%20would%20tell%20Oprah%20that%20the%20source%20of%20his%20drug%20problems%20didn't%20truly%20matter.%20He%20viewed%20his%20problems%20more%20as%20being%20a%20product%20of%20the%201960s.%20Whatever%20the%20reason%2C%20his%20drug%20use%20would%20lead%20to%20repeated%20brushes%20with%20the%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221c32ab07-7e3c-4741-924b-27f9890e54ef%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EKennedy%20graduates%20from%20Harvard%2C%20but%20drug%20use%20continues%20to%20hang%20over%20him.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20graduating%20from%20high%20school%2C%20Kennedy%20attended%20Harvard%2C%20the%20alma%20mater%20of%20his%20father%2C%20uncle%2C%20and%20grandfather.%20Like%20JFK%2C%20RFK%20Jr.%20would%20see%20his%20senior%20thesis%20turned%20into%20a%20book.%20Unfortunately%20for%20him%2C%20reviewers%20reacted%20harshly%20to%20the%20tome%20about%20federal%20judge%20Frank%20M.%20Johnson%20Jr.%2C%20whose%20rulings%20played%20a%20major%20role%20in%20the%20Civil%20Rights%20movement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20briefly%20attending%20the%20London%20School%20of%20Economics%2C%20Kennedy%20graduated%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Virginia%20Law%20School.%20While%20in%20Charlottesville%2C%20Kennedy%20met%20his%20first%20wife%2C%20Emily%20Black.%20Their%20wedding%20in%20Black's%20native%20Bloomington%2C%20Indiana%2C%20received%20international%20coverage%20as%20the%20Midwesterner%20joined%20the%20nation's%20foremost%20political%20family.%20The%20couple%20had%20two%20children%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Robert%20F.%20Kennedy%20Jr.%20is%20seen%20on%20his%20first%20wedding%20day%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F664ca02420abc1efe8fbe556%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22690%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERobert%20F.%20Kennedy%20Jr.'s%20marriage%20to%20Emily%20Black%2C%20his%20law%20school%20classmate%2C%20received%20international%20attention.%3Cp%3EImages%20Press%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20filed%20for%20divorce%20in%201994%20in%20the%20Dominican%20Republic%2C%20taking%20advantage%20of%20a%20local%20law%20that%20allows%20foreigners%20to%20file%20for%20divorce%20there%20and%20potentially%20trying%20to%20avoid%20media%20scrutiny.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20March%201982%2C%20Manhattan%20District%20Attorney%20Robert%20Morgenthau%2C%20whom%20JFK%20had%20previously%20appointed%20to%20lead%20the%20famous%20Southern%20District%20of%20New%20York%2C%20hired%20RFK%20Jr.%20as%20an%20assistant%20district%20attorney.%20The%20famous%20son's%20first%20brush%20with%20politics%20in%20New%20York%2C%20the%20state%20his%20father%20represented%20in%20the%20US%20Senate%2C%20did%20not%20go%20well.%20Kennedy%20struggled%20to%20pass%20the%20bar%20exam.%20He%20resigned%20in%20July%201983.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMonths%20later%2C%20Kennedy%20would%20spark%20his%20largest%20legal%20scandal.%20While%20on%20the%20way%20to%20receive%20treatment%20in%20South%20Dakota%20for%20his%20addiction%2C%20a%20fellow%20passenger%20found%20him%20sick%20in%20an%20airplane's%20bathroom.%20Local%20authorities%20later%20found%20a%20small%20amount%20of%20heroin%20in%20his%20belongings.%20He%20faced%20up%20to%20two%20years%20in%20prison%2C%20according%20to%20The%20New%20York%20Times.%20Kennedy%20was%20sentenced%20to%20probation%20and%20community%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fd42bb34-5aa3-47c5-ab6e-4b6d3d6503c6%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EKennedy%20found%20a%20new%20advocacy%20after%20his%20lowest%20moment.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EKennedy's%20lowest%20moment%20led%20to%20his%20greatest%20reinvention.%20As%20part%20of%20his%20community%20service%2C%20he%20worked%20for%20the%20Natural%20Resources%20Defense%20Council%20and%20was%20later%20connected%20with%20the%20Hudson%20River%20Fishermen's%20Association.%20Robert%20Boyle%2C%20founder%20of%20the%20New%20York%20environmental%20group%2C%20began%20to%20mentor%20Kennedy.%20The%20organization%20already%20had%20notched%20major%20legal%20victories%2C%20but%20Kennedy's%20star%20power%20would%20help%20take%20it%20to%20new%20heights.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20so%20committed%20to%20his%20new%20career%20that%20in%201994%2C%20he%20married%20Mary%20Richardson%2C%20a%20longtime%20friend%20of%20his%20sister%20Kerry%20Kennedy%2C%20aboard%20a%20ship%20on%20the%20Hudson%20River.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Robert%20F.%20Kennedy%20Jr.%20poses%20for%20a%20photo%20with%20actress%20Glenn%20Close%20in%20front%20of%20the%20Hudson%20River%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F664ca14c9fc063e829b32c65%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22717%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERobert%20F.%20Kennedy%20became%20a%20star%20for%20his%20environmental%20advocacy.%3Cp%3EL.%20Busacca%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20his%20relationship%20with%20Boyle%20did%20not%20last.%20His%20mentor%20later%20recalled%20that%20he%20was%20less%20than%20thrilled%20about%20the%20celebrities%20Kennedy%20soon%20brought%20onto%20the%20organization's%20board.%20He%20also%20chafed%20at%20his%20former%20proteg%C3%A9's%20other%20actions%2C%20particularly%20Kennedy's%20decision%20to%20hire%20a%20scientist%20named%20William%20Wegner.%20Kennedy%20defended%20hiring%20Wegner%2C%20who%20had%20served%20time%20in%20federal%20prison%2C%20saying%20that%20giving%20him%20a%20second%20chance%20was%20the%20right%20thing%20to%20do.%20Boyle%20was%20incensed%20given%20that%20Wegener%20was%20sentenced%20over%20his%20connections%20to%20a%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fpolitics%2F2024%2F03%2F02%2Frobert-f-kennedy-jr-rfk-riverkeeper-egg-smuggler%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20bird%20smuggling%20ring%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Boyle%20and%20seven%20other%20officials%20later%20resigned%20from%20Riverkeeper's%20board%20in%20protest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20he's%20a%20despicable%20person%2C%26quot%3B%20Boyle%20told%20Kennedy's%20unauthorized%20biographer%20in%202014.%20Boyle's%20children%20recently%20told%20The%20Washington%20Post%20that%20his%20father%20later%20couldn't%20even%20bear%20looking%20at%20the%20Hudson%20as%20it%20was%20too%20much%20of%20a%20reminder%20of%20Kennedy's%20betrayal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20Kennedy%2C%20his%20environmental%20advocacy%20became%20the%20foundation%20of%20his%20fame.%20In%201999%2C%20Time%20Magazine%20named%20Kennedy%20one%20of%20its%20%26quot%3BHeroes%20for%20the%20Planet%26quot%3B%20as%20part%20of%20a%20series%20of%20reports%20on%20leading%20environmentalists.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20gaining%20fame%2C%20Kennedy%20began%20to%20notice%20problems%20with%20his%20voice.%20He%20recently%20told%20The%20Los%20Angeles%20Times%20that%20he%20was%2042%20when%20he%20first%20noticed%20the%20problem.%20Kennedy%20was%20later%20diagnosed%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-rfk-jr-voice-raspy-cause-spasmodic-dysphonia-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Espasmodic%20dysphonia%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20rare%20neurological%20condition%20that%20affects%20muscles%20in%20one's%20voice%20box.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202010%2C%20Kennedy%20filed%20for%20divorce%20from%20Richardson%2C%20the%20mother%20of%20four%20of%20his%20six%20children.%20Two%20years%20later%2C%20she%20died%20by%20suicide%20at%20the%20couple's%20former%20Bedford%20estate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220bc52c2f-eeb4-43c1-b871-bc5e8352a934%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAfter%20years%20of%20environmentalism%2C%20Kennedy%20became%20the%20face%20of%20anti-vaccine%20advocacy.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20decades%20of%20environmental%20advocacy%2C%20Kennedy%20prepared%20to%20make%20his%20most%20contr