e%20spending%20on%20restaurants%2C%20cruises%2C%20traveling%20and%20healthcare.%20All%20these%20services%20industries%20have%20been%20expanding%20their%20payrolls%2C%20thus%20boosting%20real%20incomes%2C%20and%20fuelling%20more%20spending.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20counters%20gloomy%20expectations%20of%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecession-outlook-hard-landing-economy-consumer-spending-slowdown-growth-gdp-2024-5%5C%22%3Eimpending%20consumer%20slowdown%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20has%20been%20the%20basis%20for%20why%20the%20economy%20will%20eventually%20buckle.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20only%20the%20goods%20sector%20has%20shown%20signs%20of%20a%20growth%20recession%2C%20Yardeni%20said.%20But%20that's%20after%20the%20lockdown's%20hard-to-beat%20buying%20spree%3B%20today%2C%20goods%20spending%20remains%20at%20a%20record%20high%20when%20adjusted%20for%20inflation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20fresh%20take%20on%20what%20the%20post-war%20generation%20can%20offer%2C%20given%20that%20retirees%20are%20often%20framed%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbaby-boomer-gen-z-millennials-economy-housing-job-market-stocks-2024-2%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520baby%252Dboomer%2520%2522time%2520bomb%2Cgenerations%2520are%2520in%2520the%2520making.%5C%22%3Ea%20source%20of%20economic%20strain%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20younger%20individuals.%20With%204.1%20million%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.protectedincome.org%2Fpeak65%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eminted%20each%20year%20through%202027%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20some%20fear%20this%20will%20burden%20everything%20from%20equities%20to%20the%20labor%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20to%20Yardeni%2C%20they're%20the%20reason%20no%20consumer%20recession%20has%20appeared%20in%20the%20past%20two%20years%2C%20he%20separately%20wrote%20in%20April%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Baby%20Boomers%20watched%20a%20lot%20of%20'Star%20Trek'%20during%20t